<quantity box="[908,965,1325,1349]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1114,1325,1349]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1258,1281]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1234]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1237]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d: (A) colony; (B) detail of a branch; (C) tentacular sclerites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201122/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1101,1114,1325,1349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B) with a short stem that branches irregularly up to seven times. The branch diameter is 
<quantity box="[899,999,1361,1385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
, and some are lacking coenenchyme, exposing the dark axis. Only a very small portion of the holdfast is preserved. The polyps retract into prominent calyces up to 
<quantity box="[311,378,1433,1457]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
tall and up to 
<quantity box="[550,638,1433,1457]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
diameter (
<figureCitation box="[763,832,1433,1457]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1258,1281]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1234]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1237]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d: (A) colony; (B) detail of a branch; (C) tentacular sclerites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201122/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[817,832,1433,1457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
B), and are sparsely distributed around the branches, about 
<quantity box="[220,306,1469,1493]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
apart, and even more distant at the base of the branches and on the holdfasts, up to 
<quantity box="[1247,1312,1469,1493]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
apart (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1258,1281]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1234]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1237]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d: (A) colony; (B) detail of a branch; (C) tentacular sclerites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201122/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,1505,1529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Anthocodial armature consists of collaret and points. The collaret is composed of two whorls of long curved spindles, 
<quantity box="[258,423,1541,1565]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.41" valueMax="0.55" valueMin="0.27">0.27–0.55 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[538,702,1541,1565]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.055" valueMax="0.08" valueMin="0.03">0.03–0.08 mm</quantity>
wide, which are covered with small spines (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1279,1541,1565]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1414,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1265,1279,1541,1565]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A); the points are composed of 
<number box="[348,390,1577,1601]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
pairs of spiny spindles arranged 
<emphasis box="[771,904,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">en chevron;</emphasis>
they are 
<quantity box="[1013,1177,1577,1601]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.34" valueMin="0.16">0.16–0.34 mm</quantity>
in long and 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.035" valueMax="0.05" valueMin="0.02">0.02–0.05 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[272,339,1613,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1414,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[324,339,1613,1637]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B). The tentacles bear thorny rods, and crescents 
<quantity box="[893,1042,1613,1637]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.8999999999999999" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.145" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.09">0.09–0.2 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1154,1318,1613,1637]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.035" valueMax="0.04" valueMin="0.03">0.03–0.04 mm</quantity>
wide, that are ornamented on their convex side with tubercles and thorn-like processes (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1101,1649,1673]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1258,1281]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1234]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1237]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d: (A) colony; (B) detail of a branch; (C) tentacular sclerites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201122/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1086,1101,1649,1673]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
C). The calicular rim has two whorls of thick warty thorns that are 
<quantity box="[570,734,1685,1709]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.7999999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.24" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.18">0.18–0.30 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[847,1011,1685,1709]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.045" valueMax="0.05" valueMin="0.04">0.04–0.05 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1157,1685,1709]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1414,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1142,1157,1685,1709]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Coenenchymal sclerites comprise: small tuberculate radiates, 
<quantity box="[618,781,1721,1745]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.095" valueMax="0.12" valueMin="0.07">0.07–0.12 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[894,1057,1721,1745]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.075" valueMax="0.09" valueMin="0.06">0.06–0.09 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[1135,1203,1721,1745]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1414,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1188,1203,1721,1745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
F); crosses, 
<number box="[1338,1436,1721,1745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="0.14500000000000002" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.09">0.09–0.2</number>
diameter (
<figureCitation box="[264,330,1757,1781]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1414,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[316,330,1757,1781]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
E), with tuberculate arms; and spindles 
<quantity box="[773,921,1757,1781]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.26" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.12">0.12–0.4 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1032,1208,1757,1781]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.0875" valueMax="0.13" valueMin="0.045">0.045–0.13 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1352,1757,1781]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1414,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Heterogorgia tortuosa, lectotype, YPM 1555 d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1337,1352,1757,1781]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
D), that can be branched, straight or bent, and have the tips acute or irregularly tuberculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1325,2033]" box="[199,554,1829,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">Colour of the colony is whitish.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1325,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1864,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">Variability.</emphasis>
The other specimens examined reach up to 
<quantity box="[833,902,1865,1889]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="cm" value="14.0">14 cm</quantity>
tall, and 
<quantity box="[1010,1080,1865,1889]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
wide. The stems are connected by a continuous encrusting holdfast and subdivide close to the base into several slightly flattened branches, up to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
diameter, that re-branch often in an irregular manner. When alive, the polyps are bright yellow, and the coenenchyme looks reddish or brownish (
<figureCitation box="[545,610,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1312,1335]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,323,1291]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,323,1291]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Submarine photographs: (A – B) H. hickmani, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador (Photographs by H. P. Hickman); (C) H. tortuosa, Coiba Island, Panama; (D) H. verrucosa, Coiba Island." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201117/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[599,610,1973,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Some variation in the size of sclerites has been found in some specimens. All other characteristics are as described for the 
<typeStatus box="[765,871,2009,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201123/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" targetBox="[186,1413,193,1927]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1960,2018]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1960,1983]" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">FIGURE 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[282,509,1961,1982]" class="Anthozoa" family="Plexauridae" genus="Heterogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="36" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="tortuosa">
<emphasis box="[282,509,1961,1982]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="36">Heterogorgia tortuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lectotype, YPM 1555d, sclerites: (A) collaret spindles; (B) point spindles; (C) thorns; (D) spindles; (E) crosses; (F) radiates.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,151,320]" box="[199,1162,151,175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">The colour of the colonies is whitish to beige or brownish in ethanol or dry preserved.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,151,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[379,427,189,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName box="[545,676,189,212]" class="Anthozoa" family="Plexauridae" genus="Heterogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="tortuosa">
<emphasis box="[545,676,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. tortuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists mostly of colonies in bad condition and specimen 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34880" box="[1375,1435,189,212]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34880" name="Peabody Museum of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">YPM</collectionCode>
<number box="[151,207,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="1555.0">1555</number>
d was selected as the 
<typeStatus box="[447,550,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">lectotype</typeStatus>
to establish the species’ identity because of its better state of preservation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,151,320]" box="[199,839,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
This species is reported only for 
<collectingCountry box="[566,688,260,284]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[742,835,261,284]" name="Panama" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Panama</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,151,320]" box="[199,1246,295,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
A comparison of this species with others is included in the Remarks section for 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1239,297,320]" class="Anthozoa" family="Plexauridae" genus="Heterogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis box="[1093,1239,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. verrucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
